7. Vaticani. The theatre of Pompey, which was the only one finished at this time. stood at the south end of the Campus Martius, so looking across the Tiber on the Janiculan and Vatican hills. Juvenal (6. 344) lengthens the second syllable in Vaticanus, and he is followed by Martial.

9. Caecubum. The ⁴ Caecubus ager' was a marshy tract on the coast os Latium between Terracina and Formiae. The wines chosen to represent the finer Italian growths are two pairs of neighbouring vintages‚ one pair in‘Latium. the Caecuban and Formian (Od. 3. 16. 34); the other in Campania, the Falernian and the wine of Cales (Od. 1. 31. 9.4. 12. 14).
